		.g-s-6.post
			:markdown
				This site is compiled using the static site generator [Jekyll](jekyllrb.com "Jekyll") and hosted on [Github Pages](https://pages.github.com/ "Github Pages"). It is coded “by hand” in a effort to revive my atrophied web-development skills. To save a few key strokes, it uses [HAML](http://haml.info/ "HAML") and [SASS](https://sass-lang.com/ "SASS"). Articles are written in [Markdown](https://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/ "Markdown"). There’s nothing more complicated going on.

				Some early pages were coded with the [Atom](https://atom.io/ "Atom") code editor, but I subsequently switched back to trusty old [Coda 2](https://panic.com/coda/ "Coda 2"). I used [Figma](https://www.figma.com/ "Figma") for some early type explorations, but after that everything has been “designed in the browser”. 
				
				I write articles in [DayOne](https://dayoneapp.com/ "DayOne") and also use it to capture any stray-but-intriguing thoughts. My avatar and most article illustrations are designed in Figma. A backlog of fixes and tasks related to this site are housed in [Notion](https://notion.so "Notion").
